new,Technology Summer Internship Program: Software Engineer Intern,Citizens Bank,"Phoenix, AZ",2020-01-22,"Description

Were developing the next generation of technologists

The financial industry is evolving and Citizens is striving towards becoming a top technology destination for customers and colleagues. Our technology team is rapidly transforming by digitizing our business and driving Next-gen technology experiences for our customers.

The Technology Summer Internship Program is a critical program within Technology Services for cultivating talented, early career professionals who aspire to be future leaders.As an intern, you will assist our technologists in driving exceptional customer experiences through transformative projects and initiatives.

You have a unique opportunity to jumpstart your career through hands-on, impactful projects, comprehensive training and development, and exposure to executive leadership, paving the way for a robust career at Citizens Bank.

Software Engineer Track

As a Software Engineer Intern, you will work alongside a group of talented engineers as you gain practical experience within a broad range of initiatives. By leveraging your growing technical skills and thirst for innovation, you will help produce disruptive technologies that will ensure Citizens market leadership.

Primary responsibilities include:

Assist with designing, modifying, developing and implementing technology solutions, as well as building modern, architecturally sound components, tools and applications to meet mission-driven strategic business goals
Gain exposure to an environment rapidly transforming to the Agile methodology, adhering to best practices and collaborating effectively with your team mates.
Infuse quality of service characteristics, such as scalability, manageability and maintainability, into distributed service-based framework to create or expand business or technical capabilities.
Assist with documenting development iterations, ensuring the quality of technical documentation and creating progress reports
Participate in code and design reviews with network, infrastructure and solutions engineering teams to ensure that solutions meet current enterprise standards

NOTE: THIS INTERNSHIP PROGRAM BEGINS IN EARLY JUNE 2020

Experience during the program

In this 10-week program, you will have the opportunity to gain a strong understanding of Technology Services at Citizens Bank. Youll participate in critical projects, meet senior leaders, and enhance your technical skills as you position yourself as a possible candidate for our full-time development program.

Note: this program is based in Phoenix, AZ

As an intern in this program, we will match you with a Mentor who will help guide you through the summer program. Youll also have the opportunity to participate in a variety of activities to further develop you as a professional. Throughout the summer, youll experience:

Orientation with all Technology Services interns

Professional development workshops (such as Personal Branding and Receiving Feedback)

Weekly Senior Speaker Series with executive leadership

Social activities (such as sporting events or a bank-wide intern BBQ

Dedicated community service activities

Intern Business Challenge where youll work in small teams to solve for an organizational problem and present your recommendations to a panel of executives

Life after the program

Near the end of the program, youll be given early consideration for the full-time Technology Development Program (TDP). High performing interns interested in pursuing a career in Technology Services will have an opportunity to interview for the program before the summer ends.

The TDP is a full-time program aimed at enhancing your skills in coding, agile practices, design thinking, data management, technical knowledge of bank applications and infrastructure, and leadership. You will have the opportunity to build a rewarding and meaningful career.

