new,Lead Application Developer,Citizens Bank,"Riverside, RI",2020-01-20,"Description

The Lead Application Support resource is responsible for the full understanding of his/her system and subsystem components. This individual will act as the SME of their assigned system(s) as it relates to support, analysis, documentation and BAU activities. This individual will engage with Technology and Business Line stakeholders to coordinate and validate system patching and Qualys vulnerabilities. This individual will lead incident calls directly related to their assigned system(s) and engage with Business Line Stakeholders, Vendors and Technology partners as necessary to remediate system issues within the System Level Agreement (SLA). This individual will participate in quarterly DRET events and be available for system support during off-hours when necessary.

Additional responsibilities include executing project deliverables and maintenance system enhancements associated with software or infrastructure upgrades and ensuring company standards and policies are adhered too. This individual will identify, raise and work to mitigate current and future risk as it relates to system processing and provide risk evidence as necessary in support of Risk initiatives.

Primary responsibilities include:

Engage in troubleshooting, root cause and remediation efforts as it relates to your supported systems, inclusive of the application, database, system servers, transmissions, file shares, system processing ID's, Cron Jobs, et
