Were developing the next generation of technologists
The financial industry is evolving and Citizens is striving towards becoming a top technology destination for customers and colleagues. Our technology team is rapidly transforming by digitizing our business and driving Next-gen technology experiences for our customers.
Take advantage of this unique opportunity to be part of this exciting transformation that promises to deliver speed, efficiency and innovation for our customers. By joining our team, you will drive exceptional customer experiences through transformative projects and initiatives, from FinTech partnerships and digital payments, to modern application environments and cloud computing.
Join our Technology Development Program (TDP) and unlock your full potential!Our Technology Development Program offers comprehensive training, assignments and exposure to dynamic leaders.Jumpstart your future while helping us build the bank of the future!
Areas you will gain experience and improve your skills include but are not limited to: coding in multiple programming languages, agile practices, design thinking, data management, technical knowledge of bank applications and infrastructure, and leadership.
Software Engineer Track
The Software Engineer is responsible for the definition, design, development, implementation and support of Process Automations. This involves planning, analysis, detailed design, developing/coding, testing and implementation of all related components.
Primary responsibilities include:
Determines hardware/software systems requirements and hardware/software design. Analyzes, designs, programs, debugs, supports, and modifies software enhancements and/or new products used in Bizagi and /or Blue Prism related components.
Partners with the IT Architect during the initial stages of the project/solution to ensure the accuracy of business cases and that the solution will meet the business need.
Adheres to the established lifecycle methodology and practices in accordance to project plans while carrying out their responsibilities. This may include maintaining program libraries and technical documentation of the individual applications.
Maintains understanding of application: Reviews and validates new application solutions; Align application functionality with business requirements and strategy; Anticipates issues and challenges affecting application functionality;
Works with a team to review the quality of design and configuration, and applies judgment to plan and execute tasks.
Responds to technical queries on and around Bizagi and Blue Prism.
